parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the internal oil pump shaft can cause a loss of oil pressure and circulation, leading to extensive internal engine damage, engine seizure, and potentially deadly accidents.
symptoms: Clanking noise
no oil pressure or circulation
engine seizure
metallic fragments scoring internal engine components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clogging of the carburetor can cause the engine to cut off while driving at high speeds, leading to a loss of control and potentially deadly accidents.
symptoms: Engine cutting off while driving at high speeds
carburetor clogging.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping/ Difficulty Shifting into 2nd Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in shifting into 2nd gear can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.

difficulty getting in and out of 2nd gear
hesitation or slippage when shifting into 2nd gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Wheel Driveshaft Oil Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel driveshaft oil seal can cause oil to leak onto the rear swing arm and rear wheel, leading to loss of control, rear wheel lock-up, and potential injury or death.
symptoms: Oil leak from the rear wheel driveshaft unit
oil leaking onto the rear swing arm and rear wheel
rear differential seizing
rear wheel lock-up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the headlights while driving can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and may also lead to damage to other vehicle components.
symptoms: Headlights fall off or become loose while driving
metal pieces break at the handles
reduced visibility due to faulty headlights.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Battery and Voltage Regulator
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of batteries and voltage regulators can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The battery drains quickly
the battery fails to hold a charge
the voltage regulator fails to function properly
corrosion of components under the seat and swingarm due to battery acid leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Wheel Sprocket and Trailing Arm Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel sprocket and trailing arm can cause the rear wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The nut from the back wheel sprocket hits the trailing arm

the post that holds the nut is pulled out too far
the nut gets caught between the sprocket wheel and trailing arm
causing the rear wheel to lock up.
